@subsection CardDAV Specific Notes
Keep in mind that unlike Google Contacts, CardDAV servers do not support a
roll back feature. This means any ASynK bugs could potentially lead to loss of
information for you. While there have been no complaints of ASynK eating up
people's data, please take your own precautions before you deploy this on your
live data. The use of the @kbd{--user-dir=} option is also high encouraged.

At the moment the following fields are synched in both ways. More may be
supported over time.  @strong{Important}: Fields not mentioned here will be
lost in transit!

@enumerate  
@item
First name

@item
Last name

@item
Middle name

@item
Formatted name

@item
Suffix, Prefix

@item
Gender

@item
Email addresses

@item
Phone numbers

@item
Title

@item
Department

@item
Company name

@item
Notes

@end enumerate

Specifically, the following are not synched:

@enumerate
@item
